  "text": "Allan variance [CITATION_1] is a famous method to characterize and identify various error sources in FOG, as well as their contribution to the statistical properties of the entire noise in detail. It is very easy to obtain types of error sources and the magnitude of each error source, by using the quantitative relationship between Allan variance and the power spectrum density (PSD). Here ω(i), i = 1, 2, · · · , N, is the output angular rate of FOG, acquired at a fixed sampling period τ 0 . Then, sample the N initial samples again, with sampling time τ = M × τ 0 , where M = 1, 2, · · · , N/2. Thus, the number of data packets is K = N/M, and the average value of each time length τ is",
